OL,3,CBack in troubled water: Has P&O gone
OL,4,Crogue again?
OL,6,FIn Murphy's view, the letter suggests
OL,7,FP&O either refused to make payments
OL,8,Ffor audit work to be carried out or
OL,9,Fobstructed it.
OL,11,FEither way, he infers KPMG has
OL,12,F"serious concerns about the future
OL,13,Ffunding of P&O and that they have
OL,14,Fdrawn this concern to creditors, as
OL,15,Fthey are legally required."
OL,17,FHe adds: "Filing accounts is...both a
OL,18,Fcrime and a moral abuse of the
OL,19,Fbusiness community and society at
OL,20,Flarge".
