OL,3,CBack in troubled water: Has P&O gone
OL,4,Crogue again?
OL,6,FI asked Liam Byrne if he thought P&O
OL,7,Fis a "rogue operator" he replied:
OL,8,F"Right now, we don't know. They are
OL,9,Frogue in the sense they are breaking
OL,10,Fthe laws of the land by filing their
OL,11,Faccounts late."
OL,13,FHe added: "When safety is so
OL,14,Fimportant, we can't have companies
OL,15,Flike that operating if we can't be
OL,16,Fsure that they're financially sound.
OL,17,FRight now, we can't tell you whether
OL,18,FP&O is safe and sound".
